description:
&lt;p&gt;The Psychiatric Liaison Team based within the West Suffolk Hospital in Bury St Edmunds is looking to expand. With this we are pleased to be able offer an opportunity for you to join the passionate and dedicated team we already have in place.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a registered nurse, social worker or occupational therapist with a genuine interest in expanding your skill and knowledge base within a supportive setting, get in contact with us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Psychiatric Liaison Services works as a single point of access for referrals and provides a range of mental health specialties within one multidisciplinary team to patients aged 13 years and over. Our teams respond to a diverse range of referrals covering both the liaison and crisis assessment functions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is key to the efficient delivery of the liaison service; improving response to and management of referrals; improving knowledge and understanding of mental health issues within the hospitals; helping the team meet their key performance indicators and proactively exploring and developing partnerships and pathways to improve patient prognosis and outcome.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Post qualification experience, including acute mental health and risk management, is desirable along with the ability to demonstrate a comprehensive understanding of the differing needs of people. However individual competence and suitability will be assessed within interview with the opportunity for Band 5 clinicians to be appointed to undertake a rapid 6 month development program towards a Band 6. Significant weight during interview will be given to the values and behaviors that a candidate brings. A flexible ‘can do’ attitude, with a willingness to build links with general hospital colleagues is essential to ensure that a proactive interface is created between mental health and acute services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service’s operational hours mean you will be required to work shifts including weekends, the further plan would be to further extend into covering night time hours also. For the successful candidate part time hours would be considered as would pre-agreed shift patterns where this fits operational and service needs. Secondments would also be considered, please feel free to use the below contacts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post may include rotational working across the Crisis Pathway, but this will allow an excellent opportunity for the successful candidate to further develop their skills and experience within this clinical specialism.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We will provide a full induction and have a genuine commitment to training and development. Individual management supervision is offered and complimented by Team Clinical and Team CAMHS supervision to further support development. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We have a proud and proven culture of honesty, team involvement, and ownership of quality patient care with job satisfaction. There are will be opportunities to be involved with training, strategy and service development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits included with this role are:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;comprehensive in house &amp; external training programmes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;career progression&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;starting annual leave of 27 days per annum increasing to 33 days pa based on length of service (plus paid bank holidays)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;staff physio service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts and many more.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here at NSFT we pride ourselves on being a welcoming, talented, friendly and supportive team who like nothing better than sharing their experiences and learning from each other.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NSFT is committed to lifelong learning and continuous professional development (CPD) for its entire staff. There are a variety of definitions of CPD across the professions but it is usually taken to mean learning activities which update existing skills. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CPD is determined through appraisal with a personal development plan agreed between an individual and their manager, with the commitment of the necessary time and resources. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please find attached our Job Description and Person Specification for more detail on your Key Accountabilities, then if you feel you have what it takes to make a difference in your local communities, click APPLY!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Interview dates are to be confirmed, candidates may only be given a minimum of 3 days’ notice, please note this date is provisional and may be subject to change. You will be contacted via email and invited to book a time. These emails may go to your SPAM, so please keep checking all your emails if applying.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please visit our Facebook and Twitter page @NSFTjobs&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Tim Smith&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Service Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address tim.smith@nsft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01284 719700&lt;/p&gt;
